name: river-restoration-data-in-lamoille-county-vermont
notes: Documented river and riparian buffer restoration projects in Lamoille County, Vermont. Restoration includes buffer plantings (trees and shrubs), bank stabilization (rock, tree revetments, willow), fencing, bank shaping, and instream habitat features. The work is funded and performed in cooperation with the local agricultural community, and local, state, and federal government agencies.
